
I brought this up with a new doctor and they said "well it''s rare you probably don''t have it" üôÑ she reluctantly gave me a referral after I demanded one. I''m now on a 20 MONTH wait list to be evaluated.

I''m just so frustrated that it was never written on my chart and now that I''m older I''m suffering and being retraumatized by all this.

Sharing to rant but if anyone has advice or similar stories please share. ', 'Technology & Software', 'ehlersdanlos', 3, 53, 5.3, '$800M-$2.5B', 'online', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'open', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, FALSE, 'active', '2025-12-15 17:50:24.226892+00:00', '2025-12-15 22:55:24.217990+00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2025-12-17 00:34:31.395184', 72, 'Medical record mismanagement creates 19-year diagnostic limbo for chronic condition patients', '$800M-$2.5B', 'medium', 'high', 'Chronic illness patients (ages 25-50) navigating complex multi-specialist care systems', 9, '["Patient-controlled medical record platform with AI verification of verbal diagnoses vs. written documentation", "Care coordination service specifically for rare disease patients to ensure diagnostic continuity across providers", "Telemedicine platform connecting rare disease patients with specialists, reducing 20-month waits to weeks"]', '["Focus on rare/complex conditions where documentation gaps cause severe harm and lengthy delays", "Patient advocacy layer that bridges communication gaps between verbal diagnoses and formal documentation", "Built-in specialist matching algorithm to reduce catastrophic wait times for confirmatory evaluations"]', '["HIPAA compliance complexity and liability concerns around medical record management and verification", "Difficulty acquiring users in fragmented rare disease communities; high customer acquisition costs", "Physicians may resist third-party platforms challenging their documentation practices"]', '["Survey 200+ rare disease patients about documentation gaps and diagnostic delays; validate if hEDS community pain generalizes", "Interview 15-20 specialists in genetics/rare diseases about documentation workflows and pain points with record continuity", "Build MVP: Simple patient portal for tracking verbal vs. written diagnoses with automated provider follow-up requests", "Partner with 2-3 rare disease advocacy organizations (EDS Society, NORD) for initial user base and credibility"]', 'Medical Records Validation & Continuity Platform for Chronic Patients', 'Patients with complex chronic conditions face documentation gaps when verbal diagnoses aren''t formally recorded, leading to years of delayed care, retraumatization, and difficulty accessing specialists. The disconnect between patient experience and medical records creates barriers to continuity of care, especially when changing providers.', '{"original_title" : "\"Lost\" hEDS diagnosis", "original_body" : "When I was 13 I was evaluated for hEDS and was told verbally that I have it as well as MCAS and dysautonamia. So I''ve lived my life as if it''s have it because, well I''m 99.9% sure I do and a doctor told me.\n\nI''m 32 now and parsing through my medical records and there is no mention of hEDS, MCAS or anything - dispite symptoms being noted almost every visit.\n\nI brought this up with a new doctor and they said \"well it''s rare you probably don''t have it\" üôÑ she reluctantly gave me a referral after I demanded one. I''m now on a 20 MONTH wait list to be evaluated.\n\nI''m just so frustrated that it was never written on my chart and now that I''m older I''m suffering and being retraumatized by all this.\n\nSharing to rant but if anyone has advice or similar stories please share. ", "subreddit" : "r/technology_and_software", "upvotes" : 53, "comments" : 17, "platform" : "reddit", "url" : "", "confidence_score" : 0.85}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO opportunities (id, title, description, category, subcategory, severity, validation_count, growth_rate, market_size, geographic_scope, country, region, city, completion_status, solution_description, solved_at, solved_by, feasibility_score, duplicate_of, author_id, is_anonymous, status, created_at, updated_at, source_id, source_url, source_platform, ai_analyzed, ai_analyzed_at, ai_opportunity_score, ai_summary, ai_market_size_estimate, ai_competition_level, ai_urgency_level, ai_target_audience, ai_pain_intensity, ai_business_model_suggestions, ai_competitive_advantages, ai_key_risks, ai_next_steps, ai_generated_title, ai_problem_statement, raw_source_data, latitude, longitude, demographics, search_trends, demographics_fetched_at) VALUES (109, 'Finally off Fycompa after 2 years.', 'Trileptal for 10 years? I have always been on maximum dosage of Trileptal, 1,800 mg per day. It didn''t help too much (200 intense deja vu per day, \~20+ half-body seizure per year.)

Since November 2023, I have also been taking **Fycompa 2 mg** **(only!)** per day. It works well for my seizures ‚Äì they have reduced by about half and are less intense, which means fewer bruises and less tongue biting. I really appreciate this effect.

Fycompa seems to have intensified gradually. My personality has become very **dark, tense, and even more negative**. I often feel short of breath and find myself constantly thinking about the worst possible outcomes.

I started seeing a counsellor, but the ‚Äúfeel good‚Äù feeling only lasts a few days before I drop back into the same emotional ‚Äúpit‚Äù. **Almost dysfunctional at work and becoming the weirdo in the office.**

On good days I can function, but **even small triggers can make me extremely angry. Minor frustrations can send me straight to thoughts like ‚Äúit‚Äôs time to die‚Äù.** My husband was so frustrated that he has an affair - because I have been blaming him too much every single day. 

I have tried 2-3 suicide methods (hanging and plastic bag suffocation), and keep Googling/ChatGPT on similar topics.

My psychiatrist has discouraged the use of mood stabilizers because he is worried that I might overdose on them.

Eventually, and very sadly, I talked with my neurologist today, and we agreed to stop Fycompa. It really is a **love‚Äìhate relationship.** I am grateful that Fycompa has helped my seizures so much, but it may also be the reason I have become even more emotionally unstable and distressed over these past two years.

I also want to quit my job now..as a new start after taking off Fycompa.

**Trileptal was bad too in terms of suicidal ideation, but Fycompa has definitely made it much more more frequent and real.**

Fycompa user - any similar experience?', 'Technology & Software', 'Epilepsy', 2, 2, 0.2, '$800M-$2B', 'online', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'open', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, FALSE, 'active', '2025-12-15 17:50:24.226892+00:00', '2025-12-15 23:12:00.903837+00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2025-12-17 00:34:37.471617', 72, 'Critical gap in epilepsy medication side effect tracking and mental health support for patients', '$800M-$2B', 'low', 'critical', 'Epilepsy patients on anti-seizure medications (3.4M in US, 50M globally)', 10, '["B2B SaaS platform for neurologists to monitor patient mental health alongside seizure control", "Patient-facing app with mood tracking, medication journaling, and early warning systems for psychiatric side effects", "Data analytics service selling anonymized insights to pharmaceutical companies for post-market surveillance"]', '["First-mover in specialized epilepsy medication mental health monitoring vs generic health apps", "Built-in community validation and peer support from patients experiencing similar side effects", "Critical safety gap that neurologists currently lack tools to address systematically", "Potential FDA/regulatory interest in improved adverse event reporting for psychiatric symptoms"]', '["Liability concerns when dealing with suicidal patients - requires robust medical oversight and crisis protocols", "HIPAA compliance complexity and need for medical device/digital health regulatory clearance", "Difficult sales cycle requiring buy-in from both neurologists and psychiatrists across specialties", "Patient acquisition challenge as epilepsy is relatively rare and highly fragmented across medications"]', '["Interview 20-30 epilepsy patients and neurologists to validate medication side effect monitoring gap", "Analyze FDA adverse event database for psychiatric symptoms across top 10 anti-seizure medications", "Prototype simple mood/symptom tracking tool and test with epilepsy support groups", "Consult healthcare attorney on regulatory pathway and liability mitigation strategies", "Research partnership opportunities with epilepsy foundations and neurology practices"]', 'Epilepsy Medication Side Effect Tracker & Mental Health Monitor', 'Epilepsy patients on complex medication regimens like Fycompa struggle to track gradual psychological side effects that emerge over time, making it difficult to connect mental health changes to specific medications or dosages. Current tools don''t adequately help patients and doctors identify when medication benefits are outweighed by quality-of-life deteriorating side effects.', '{"original_title" : "Finally off Fycompa after 2 years.", "original_body" : "Trileptal for 10 years? I have always been on maximum dosage of Trileptal, 1,800 mg per day. It didn''t help too much (200 intense deja vu per day, \\~20+ half-body seizure per year.)\n\nSince November 2023, I have also been taking **Fycompa 2 mg** **(only!)** per day. It works well for my seizures ‚Äì they have reduced by about half and are less intense, which means fewer bruises and less tongue biting. I really appreciate this effect.\n\nFycompa seems to have intensified gradually. My personality has become very **dark, tense, and even more negative**. I often feel short of breath and find myself constantly thinking about the worst possible outcomes.\n\nI started seeing a counsellor, but the ‚Äúfeel good‚Äù feeling only lasts a few days before I drop back into the same emotional ‚Äúpit‚Äù. **Almost dysfunctional at work and becoming the weirdo in the office.**\n\nOn good days I can function, but **even small triggers can make me extremely angry. Minor frustrations can send me straight to thoughts like ‚Äúit‚Äôs time to die‚Äù.** My husband was so frustrated that he has an affair - because I have been blaming him too much every single day. \n\nI have tried 2-3 suicide methods (hanging and plastic bag suffocation), and keep Googling/ChatGPT on similar topics.\n\nMy psychiatrist has discouraged the use of mood stabilizers because he is worried that I might overdose on them.\n\nEventually, and very sadly, I talked with my neurologist today, and we agreed to stop Fycompa. It really is a **love‚Äìhate relationship.** I am grateful that Fycompa has helped my seizures so much, but it may also be the reason I have become even more emotionally unstable and distressed over these past two years.\n\nI also want to quit my job now..as a new start after taking off Fycompa.\n\n**Trileptal was bad too in terms of suicidal ideation, but Fycompa has definitely made it much more more frequent and real.**\n\nFycompa user - any similar experience?", "subreddit" : "r/technology_and_software", "upvotes" : 2, "comments" : 1, "platform" : "reddit", "url" : "", "confidence_score" : 0.85}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
